textBox.richText: Pano was scheduled to open today, so I headed straight over there after dropping off Max at Freestyle. Got early tracks...the trees under the lift were good, but you couldn’t turn or you’d stop. The far side of the bowl was pretty good; did some laps through there before meeting up with Gunter and Michelle. We did a lap through the switchyard trees before heading over to Vasquez. The best snow, though, was under pine cliffs. Did an unintentional 3:57 game (Iron Horse), along with one last run with Gunter through there. Fun vid below of us playing around. :)
